observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:
Direct the Inventory Committee  to conduct the actual count of the properties of the municipality;
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to prepare the report on the results of the count using the prescribed form and reconcile the same with accounting records so that the correctness of the account balances can be ascertained;
Direct the Municipal Treasurer as Property Custodian and the Municipal Accountant to maintain stock cards and ledgers cards, respectively to support the amount of PPE and inventories;
Request the Municipal Agricultural Officer to conduct periodic inventory and monitoring on livestock dispersals.
